@borsss — thanks for trying out Autonomy. The way linked wallets work is that you're able to view the NFTs  from another wallet address without needing to import the seed for that address into Autonomy. However, since we don't have your seed for that address, we can't handle the signing requests needed to connect that address to a dapp. In other words, linked accounts only have view-only permissions in Autonomy. If you want to also be able to sign from that address, you'll need to import your seed into Autonomy. If you do want to import your seed, the screenshots below will walk you through the process.
@borsss

Thanks, will give it a go. I think it might be useful to review the onboarding UX for users with existing wallets, perhaps having `Import an existing Wallet` as a new top-level menu ("I already have a Tezos/Ethereum wallet and I want to use it to collect NFTs & sign transactions with Autonomy") alongside the existing `Link an existing wallet`   which appears to be the view-only option.
this is great feedback. I'll let @Naixm followup on this with you.

Thanks, @borsss. It's a new UI, so we appreciate you pointing out any places that you find confusing. We'll work on it. When I was putting together the screenshots, I also felt it could be a lot clearer.
